<headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 08 at 3:41PM ADT  by NWS San Juan</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of the San Juan
metropolitan area and northeastern municipalities through 415 PM
AST...
At 238 PM AST, a strong thunderstorm was over Trujillo Alto, moving
east at 10 mph. This thunderstorm is expected to regenerate as it
moves over northeastern Puerto Rico. Torrential rains from this
activity could lead to ponding of water on roadways and poorly
drained areas to rapid rises along small streams.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
